{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c5888198-7e41-4919-99ca-d0cc9cc5d7a6","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2**, which supports constructor injection for `TestContext`. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialize, IAsyncCleanup\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Synchronous init — constructor injection for TestContext\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async init — runs before each test (like [TestInitialize])\n    public async Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        await Task.CompletedTask; // your async setup\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup — runs after each test (like [TestCleanup])\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        await Task.CompletedTask; // your async teardown\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_testContext);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — inject `TestContext`; use for synchronous setup (field init, config).\n- **`IAsyncInitialize`** — implement `InitializeAsync()` for async per-test setup (DB connections, HTTP clients, etc.).\n- **`IAsyncCleanup`** — implement `CleanupAsync()` for async per-test teardown.\n- These interfaces replace the `[TestInitialize]`/`[TestCleanup]` attributes with a more natural, DI-friendly pattern.\n\nFor **class-level** async setup, use `[ClassInitialize]` / `[ClassCleanup]` as static methods alongside this pattern.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fa2d60d4-17f6-4171-855f-80b287db3ca3","outputTokens":401,"requestId":"5802:3E4B47:37530C5:3B089B1:6A0338AC"},"id":"d9b368da-fd56-4504-a3ed-09c586faccdf","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:27:02.848Z","parentId":"07883b44-7dbb-4882-b8ca-3f7780b684d5"}
